text: Kents Pocket is a locality in the Scenic Rim Region, Queensland, Australia. ==Census Data== Kents Pocket has a population of 24 at the . The locality contains 10 households, in which 51.7% of the population are males and 48.3% of the population are females with a median age of 50, 12 years above the national average. The average weekly household income is $2,124, $688 above the national average. == References == Category:Scenic Rim Region Category:Localities in Queensland
